        [
          "A con-artist whose last scam may have gone a bit too far.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Jenn Wolfe"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You may have taken things a bit too far.\n\nBetween the foster homes you grew up in and the rough streets you roamed on, you had to always be making a play just to survive. It wasn't as if you were little and said \"I want to be a con-artist\" when I grow up, but it was how you got by. If there is a scam out there, you've run it, and you were pretty good at it too. Good enough to not get caught, at least. For a while there, when the whole \"ghost hunter\" craze took off, you ran one where you were a \"para-psychologist\" who would get in touch with the ghosts of the dead and comfort grieving family members about it. That sort of blew up into hunting the dead in old houses with people who thought this stuff was real. You sold your services, you made a pretty penny. And then the Tremere came calling, curious about your abilities. Your own story may have gotten away from you a bit, because they decided you'd be a perfect person to embrace.\n\nWell, the joke is on you now! You weren't able to see ghosts before and now, you are haunted by them, which is both creepy and annoying, especially as you don't even know what to do about it. Worse, you are now fighting to survive in a clan full of weird, vampire/magey/doomseday survivialists who thought you were some sort of medium and you weren't - at least you weren't then. Before your Embrace, you didn't have an announce of magic in you for real. Now, you have learned quickly, picking up Thaumaturgy and the occult, if nothing else just to keep your head above water. Besides, it could prove to be useful, right? Maybe you can figure out a way to parlay that into something, right, especially with all the dark things you hear whispered about.\n\nWhat you hadn't banked on was that this clan was so big on rank and file, and you've been transferred out of Five Burroughs Chantry in New York to Los Angeles Chantry. You've arrived here without a clue to the situation, outside of a report saying something about demons and some ritual some Lord cast and that apparently there is angels there, crazy shit. You have a couple of buddies out here, at least, friends from the con games of old, and some influences from your days running scams. You aren't completely uprooted and destitute on this cost. But, the deeper you get into this Tremere, vampire crazy, the harder it is to swim. You just need to keep spinning all your plates!"
        ],
        [
